#SushiLover Who wants salmon? 🍣🍣🍣

Hubby and I love Japanese food but we have high standards when it comes to eating raw dishes since we both worked in Japan and we can compare the freshness and the authenticity of the sushi.

Finally, we discovered Salmon HQ that checked all our expectations when it came to freshness and premium quality ingredients of sushi. 

We tried their Premium Salmon Cake and 3 of their Healthy Heart Specials at talaga namang mapapa OISHI ka sa sarap at freshness.🫰

🍣𝐏𝐫𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐮𝐦 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐂𝐚𝐤𝐞- layers of premium kani kama mixed with ebiko, premium spicy salmon and chuka wakame mixed with japanese sushi rice.

#ExplorersinTandem Milestone! Long post ahead.

Finally, we were able to leave them in #kidschurch though meron pa din kaming konting drama ni Kuya when I’m about to leave. 

Kuya to me: Don’t go, watch me outside with teary eyed pa🥹(me smiling inside diko alam if mag-give in ba ako sa teary eyed nya)

Me: Kuya, inay needs to be outside. I’ll watch over you.(Leave them when I got the chance to and attend the service with itay. 😊)

Infairness nakikinig naman sila sa teacher in front.

That face when you successfully created your own coloring page the way you want it to be! 

Another milestone for our #littleexplorer as he created this printable with minimal support from inay.
I asked him how he feel about it and he happily answered I did it and asked me to take picture of it  so he can show it to itay and our relatives. This is not to brag but showing his achievements to them make him happy and acknowledged. 😍

Side story: We usually create printable for them to color. At first, I do it by myself until they wanted to get involved and tell me what to put in the printable. Tbh, I was hesitant b’coz it will took longer and I get annoyed with their so many requests and revisions ‘coz time is gold and I have lot of things in mind. Then I realized, I should enjoy this moment because this is a precious moment that I can looked back to when they can finally make their own and they don’t need me anymore.(nakaka-emo time is gold nga talaga😅)

Btw, Ric also made his but forgot to take picture of him.

Just sharing this to remind us that it’s okay to involve them in your chores even if it means additional hour and mess. Just enjoyed it because time passes by so fast that you’ll gonna miss this moment with them. 
Also, by letting them involved you are molding them to be an independent and better individuals. 

Proverbs 22:6 Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old he will not depart from it.
